Sandon County was named in honour of Dudley Ryder , First Earl of Harrowby and Viscount Sandon (1762-1847).
Sandon County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is centred on Armidale , and also includes Uralla .
